Axel
Axel is a student who appears to be daydreaming and chill, but surprisingly excels in his studies without much apparent effort.

Mia
Mia is Axel's friend who studies hard and is initially perplexed by Axel's academic success.

Josh
Josh is Axel's friend who studies and is surprised by Axel's test scores.

Mr. Hargrove
Mr. Hargrove is the teacher who lectured about Napoleon.

Napoleon
Napoleon is a historical figure discussed in Mr. Hargrove's lesson, which Axel found interesting.

School
The setting where Axel and his friends are students, and where Mr. Hargrove teaches.

Homework
School assignments that Axel doesn't stress over.

Textbooks
Learning materials that other students use for studying.

Tests
Evaluations of students' knowledge, which Axel consistently performs well on.

Lesson
A period of instruction during which Mr. Hargrove teaches and Axel remembers key details.

Superheroes
A subject Axel draws during lessons.

Tips
Advice on how to study and learn effectively.

Learning
The process of acquiring knowledge and understanding, which Axel approaches in a unique way.

Facts
Pieces of information that Axel absorbs like a sponge.

Michelangelo di Lodovico Buonarroti Simoni
Italian sculptor, painter, architect, and poet of the High Renaissance, born in the Republic of Florence. His work was inspired by classical antiquity and had a lasting influence on Western art. He is considered an archetypal Renaissance man.

Republic of Florence
A historical state in Italy where Michelangelo was born.

Leonardo da Vinci
Rival and elder contemporary of Michelangelo, also considered an archetypal Renaissance man.

PietÃ 
One of Michelangelo's best-known sculptures, created before the age of 30.

David
One of Michelangelo's best-known sculptures, created before the age of 30.

Genesis
Scenes from Genesis on the ceiling of the Sistine Chapel in Rome, one of Michelangelo's most influential frescoes.

Sistine Chapel
A chapel in Rome where Michelangelo created the Genesis frescoes.

Rome
City where the Sistine Chapel is located.

The Last Judgment
Michelangelo's fresco on the altar wall of the Sistine Chapel.

Laurentian Library
Michelangelo's design of the Laurentian Library pioneered Mannerist architecture.

Antonio da Sangallo the Younger
Architect of St. Peter's Basilica whom Michelangelo succeeded.

St. Peter's Basilica
Michelangelo became the architect of St. Peter's Basilica at the age of 71 and transformed its plan.

Giorgio Vasari
Biographer who proposed that Michelangelo's work transcended that of any artist living or dead.

Il Divino
A title meaning 'the divine one,' often used to refer to Michelangelo.<SEP>An honorific title meaning 'the divine one,' used to describe Michelangelo during his lifetime.

Mannerism
A short-lived movement in Western art between the High Renaissance and the Baroque, influenced by attempts to imitate Michelangelo's style.

Michelangelo
Italian sculptor, painter, architect, and poet of the High Renaissance. Known for his influence on Western art and mastery in various artistic fields.

High Renaissance
A period in European history characterized by a revival of classical art and culture. Michelangelo was a prominent figure of this era.

Western Art
Artistic traditions and styles originating in Europe and later spread to other parts of the world. Michelangelo's work significantly influenced this tradition.

16th Century
The century in which Michelangelo lived and worked, during which he became one of the best-documented artists.

Biographers
Individuals who wrote about Michelangelo's life and accomplishments during and after his lifetime.

Western End
The western portion of St. Peter's Basilica, which was completed to Michelangelo's design.

Dome of St. Peter's Basilica
A major architectural feature of St. Peter's Basilica, designed by Michelangelo and completed after his death.

Three Biographies
Multiple accounts of Michelangelo's life published during his lifetime, indicating his fame and recognition.

TerribilitÃ 
Michelangelo's ability to instill a sense of awe in viewers of his art, a key characteristic of his artistic style.

Subsequent Artists
Artists who followed Michelangelo and attempted to imitate his expressive physicality, contributing to the rise of Mannerism.

Baroque
A later period in Western art that followed Mannerism.

Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)
A technique enabling generative AI models to retrieve and incorporate new information, modifying interactions with LLMs to reference a specified set of documents.

Gen AI
Generative Artificial Intelligence models that can benefit from the RAG technique.

Large Language Model (LLM)
A type of AI model that RAG enhances by incorporating information retrieval before generating responses.

Ars Technica
A source of information, mentioned in the text, that explains RAG as a way of improving LLM performance by blending the LLM process with a web search or other document look-up process.

AI Hallucinations
Instances where AI chatbots invent policies or lawyers cite nonexistent legal cases, which RAG helps reduce.

User Queries
Questions or requests submitted by users to a large language model, which RAG helps the model answer more accurately.

Chatbot
An application using AI, potentially benefitting from RAG to access internal company data and provide more informed responses.

Internal Company Data
Proprietary information held within a company, which RAG allows chatbots to access.

Web Sources
External data repositories from which RAG can pull relevant text.

Databases
Structured collections of data that RAG can use to retrieve relevant text.

Uploaded Documents
Documents loaded into a system, which RAG can search to find relevant information.

Authoritative Sources
Reputable and reliable sources of information used by RAG to generate responses.

Static Training Data
The fixed dataset used to train traditional LLMs, which RAG supplements with new information.

Investor Confidence
The level of assurance investors have in the market, impacted by factors like Federal Reserve policy.

Real-World Issues
Problems and complications that arise from AI hallucinations, such as incorrect legal citations.

Policies
Rules or guidelines invented by AI chatbots, which RAG seeks to prevent.

Lawyers
Legal professionals who have cited nonexistent legal cases due to AI hallucinations.

Legal Cases
Court proceedings or rulings that have been misrepresented or fabricated by AI chatbots.

IMAP Mailboxes
IMAP mailboxes are email storage locations that users may have multiple of, from which emails are fetched.

Classifier Module
The classifier module is a component that processes emails received from IMAP mailboxes.

AI-LLM Technology
AI-LLM technology is used to classify and analyze emails, leveraging large language models.

Customer Request
Customer Request is a category label for emails indicating a customer inquiry or request.

Customer Complaint
Customer Complaint is a category label for emails indicating a customer grievance.

Normal Priority
Normal Priority is a classification level for emails based on their urgency.

High Priority
High Priority is a classification level for emails based on their urgency.

Open Source LLM
Open Source LLM refers to freely available large language models that can be used for email classification.

Gemini
Gemini is an example of an open-source large language model that can be used for email classification.

Llama3.1
Llama3.1 is an example of an open-source large language model that can be used for email classification.

Ollama
Ollama is mentioned as a local LLM solution that can be used.

Groq-API
Groq-API is mentioned as a solution that can be used.

Emails
Emails are electronic messages that are fetched from IMAP mailboxes and processed by the classifier module.

User
The user is the individual who owns the email addresses and interacts with the email client.

Email Threads
Chains of related emails regarding a specific topic or issue.<SEP>Email threads are a series of related emails on the same topic.

Category Labels
Category labels are tags assigned to emails to classify their content.

Tags
Tags are labels assigned to emails to classify their content.

IMAP Inbox
The IMAP inbox is the primary location for receiving and storing emails.

Dashboard
A dashboard is a visual interface for displaying email statistics and information.

Email Client
An email client is software used to access and manage emails, such as Outlook or Thunderbird.

Outlook
Outlook is a popular email client software.

Thunderbird
Thunderbird is a popular email client software.

Config File
A config file stores configuration settings, such as category definitions and LLM system prompts.

System Prompt
The system prompt is instructions provided to the LLM to guide its email classification process.

Order Numbers
Order numbers are specific pieces of information extracted from emails.

Invoice Numbers
Invoice numbers are specific pieces of information extracted from emails.

Customer Numbers
Customer numbers are specific pieces of information extracted from emails.

SP
SP is an organization providing a customers CSV file with a fixed format for customer identification.<SEP>SP is an organization that provides a customers CSV file with a fixed format.<SEP>Service Providers, who reply to client emails.

Python
Python is a programming language recommended for use in software development.<SEP>Python is the recommended programming language for the software development architecture.

REST-API
REST-API is a type of interface that could be used for communication with the web server.<SEP>REST-API is an interface that can be defined to communicate with the web server.

Customers CSV File
A Customers CSV File is a file containing customer information, used to determine if a customer is new or existing.

Web Application
The front end of the software should be a pure web application.

SP evidio dashboard
SP evidio dashboard is a dashboard where the results can be integrated and visualised.

Web Server
The Web Server is a server where the front end is located. The software should be able to integrate into the SP evidio dashboard somehow.

Email
Electronic messages used for communication with customers, suppliers, and authorities.<SEP>Email is the form of communication that is analyzed to provide statistics, including the number of emails per category and processing status (unread, read, replied, etc.).

Statistics
Data about the number of emails per category, per day, used for tracking and analysis.<SEP>Statistics represents the data on email volume and processing status (unread, read, replied, etc.) sorted by date/time categories, which needs to be stored, tracked and visualized.

Service Providers
Entities offering services, aiming to improve email communication with customers, suppliers, and authorities.

Customers
Clients or individuals who receive services from the Service Providers.

Suppliers
Entities that provide resources or materials to the Service Providers.

Authorities
Governmental or regulatory bodies that interact with the Service Providers.

AI-LLM Component
Artificial Intelligence Language Model component designed to track email threads and provide summaries of event processing status.

Admin
The administrator is responsible for configuring and defining procedures for full automation by the system.

Email Classification System
A system designed for Service Providers to categorize emails and improve communication.

Project
The development initiative to create an email classification system.

Email Priority
The level of importance assigned to an email: Normal or High.

Customer Issue
A problem or query raised by a customer.

Customer Database
A repository of customer information used to identify existing or new customers.

Event Tickets
Records created for each event, used for tracking and management.

Event/Ticket
An occurrence or issue that requires attention and tracking.

Processing Status
The current stage of an event or issue being addressed.

Automation Feature
A capability to automatically process and reply to emails based on their category.

Drafts
Suggested email responses generated by the system for manual approval.

Procedures
Defined steps or processes that can be fully automated by the system.

Client
A customer who sends a complaint email.

Tokyo Metropolis
Tokyo Metropolis is the official name of Tokyo.<SEP>Tokyo Metropolis, also known as Tokyo, is the capital and most populous city.

China
A country mentioned in the text.<SEP>A country with a very large population.

Greater Tokyo Area
The Greater Tokyo Area includes Tokyo and parts of six neighboring prefectures and is the most populous metropolitan area in the world.

Tokyo
Tokyo is the capital and most populous city.

2023
The year when the population of Tokyo proper was over 34 million.

2024
The year when the population of the Greater Tokyo Area was 41 million.
